\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Service Improvement Register
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Service Improvement Register (SIR) is the authoritative record of the Department's improvement intake and triage activity.
 The Assistant IT Director shall maintain the SIR in the System of Engagement.
 Each SIR entry shall record,
 at minimum:
 the improvement identified,
 the intake source,
 the date logged,
 the triage decision,
 the linked work order or project record number,
 and closure confirmation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The SIR is a log.
 Once a SIR entry is routed and a work order or project record is linked,
 execution is governed entirely by the receiving policy.
 SIR entries shall remain linked to an active work order or project record from the time of routing through closure.
 Where a linked work order or project is cancelled,
 the Assistant IT Director shall formally close the SIR entry with a cancellation notation and IT Director authorization documented in the entry.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
SIR records shall be retained for a minimum of two (2) calendar years from the end of the calendar year in which the entry was created,
 in accordance with NRS 239.125 and the Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule:
 LRDA 20071558 (Activity Reports).
\end_layout

